Mindblowing lyrics and well composed, I'm an Indian and I'm proud to be one but that doesn't stop me respecting virtues or other countries, especially, Pakistan, though, apart, both India and Pakistan share similarities in many aspects of life, Music for one, I surely love Coke Studio India and I can't contain my curiosity when any new song comes in, I do not have time to sit in front of TV sets, watching Coke Studio, I prefer using Internet after wee office hours (Well, call it a liberty of owning a business).

Just logged in to find this wonderful song composed for mother earth, I do not remember, how many times I've listened it till now but believe me, this one's too going into my personal collection.

Lastly, Coke Studio Pakistan, please do not forget to bring the magical drummer in season 8, the one with those curly hairs, very energetic guy, I'm a keyboardist, had performed while I was studying but now I'm keeping my music reserved to myself.
And yeah, why would I miss a chance to wish you 'Happy Independence Day' while we Indians celebrate it tomorrow.

snippet.textDisplay:
i would respectfully disagree with some comments. The humble request to indian audience is that, do appreciate our talent it develops mutual respect among ppl. however, the music and ppl belong to pakistan and they work really hard for positive projection of this nation and not for personal glorification. I hope the day comes when indians broadcast to world that their music, movies and/or other talents are as south Asian thing rather than "indian only" thing that day coke studio will be as indian thing as it is Pakistani thing. 
This song reminds of great words that our Nation's founder said "The Story of Pakistan, its struggle and its achievement, is the very story of great human ideals, struggling to survive in the face of great odds and difficulties"
Meray Mulk tu hamesha abad rahay, yeh jaan to ani jani hai. 
Happy independence to Both my Nation and to nation of India.
